y' = xy
y(x) = c_1\,e^\frac{x^2}{2}
y'=dy/dx
xy
\frac{dy}{dx}=xy\Leftrightarrow \frac{1}{y}\frac{dy}{dx}=x\Leftrightarrow\int\frac{1}{y}\frac{dy}{dx}{dx}=\int x\ dx
\Leftrightarrow\int \frac{dy}{y}=\frac{x^{2}}{2}+c\Leftrightarrow ln(y)=\frac{x^{2}}{2}+c 
y=e^{x^{2}/2 + c}=Ae^{x^{2}/2}
A
A=e^{c}
\frac{dy}{dx} = xy
\frac{dy}{y} = xdx
y = \frac{x^2}{2} + c
y = e^c e^\frac{x^2}{2}
